# Do not silently delete suspicious code

Never silently delete code paths that appear dead or wrong. If a path
looks buggy, add a `# TODO(bug):` comment describing the symptom and
suspected cause, and leave the behavior unchanged unless explicitly
asked to fix the bug.

The marker has three required parts: the literal `# TODO(bug):`
prefix, a one-line description of the **symptom** (what the user
observes when the bug fires), and a follow-up sentence on the
**suspected cause** (which invariant the code currently violates).
A future contributor must be able to grep `TODO(bug):` and triage
each hit without rereading the surrounding logic.

One live `# TODO(bug):` marker is in the tree at present:

- the desktop-export auth-token omission in
  `cursor_view/desktop/api.py::DesktopApi.save_export` (in desktop mode
  the native "Save as..." dialog completes and the user picks a path,
  but no file is written and the UI surfaces an HTTP 401 error). The
  method builds a loopback `GET /api/chat/<id>/export` and reads it with
  `urllib.request.urlopen`, but that in-process request carries neither
  the `X-Cursor-View-Token` header (the frontend's `useDesktopAuth` sets
  it on axios only, not on Python's `urllib`) nor the `cursor-view-token`
  cookie (no cookie jar on a bare `urlopen`), so the `install_auth`
  `before_request` gate added in Improvement 10 401s the request and
  `urlopen` raises into the `except` that returns `{"saved": False,
  "error": ...}`. `save_export` predates the auth gate and was never
  updated to attach `self._token` to its own loopback call. Surfaced by
  the Improvement 18 implementation bug sweep and left behavior-unchanged
  per this rule rather than fixed in the sweep.

